---

<section class="relative bg-brand-surface-dark overflow-hidden">
  <div class="absolute inset-0">
    <img
      src="https://picsum.photos/seed/watch+gears+workshop+macro/1920/800"
      alt="Watch manufacture workshop"
      class="w-full h-full object-cover opacity-40"
    />
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-r from-brand-surface-dark via-brand-surface-dark/90 to-brand-surface-dark/60"></div>
  </div>

  <div class="relative z-10 max-w-[1440px] mx-auto grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-12 items-center min-h-[560px] md:min-h-[640px] py-24 md:py-32 px-6 md:px-10 lg:px-16">
    <div class="md:col-span-6 lg:col-span-5 text-white">
      <p class="text-label text-white/50 mb-5">Manufacture</p>
      <h2 class="text-display-lg font-bold mb-8">Made in City. Not assembled.</h2>
      <div class="space-y-5 text-body text-white/75 max-w-lg">
        <p>
          Every Formd movement is designed, assembled, and regulated in our own workshops. We do not source calibers from third parties — we build them from the ground up.
        </p>
        <p>
          The difference is visible in every detail of the finish. The bridges, the screws, the winding rotor: each part is made to be seen.
        </p>
      </div>
      <a
        href="/watchmaking"
        class="inline-block mt-10 border border-white/80 text-white text-label px-7 py-3.5 hover:bg-white hover:text-brand-surface-dark transition-colors duration-300"
      >
        How we make them
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
